<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style="font-size: 12pt;"><div style="font-size: 12pt;"><div style="font-size: 12pt;"><div style="font-size: 12pt;"><div style="font-size: 12pt;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br><br>Thank you for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.<br><br><b>We can see that you’ve made a request to cancel your insurance policy.</b>&nbsp;Before we go ahead and cancel your policy for you, we want to make sure that you fully understand what your current cover includes and to confirm that you’re aware of the financial risks of not holding insurance.<br><br>Please note that as per our terms and conditions,&nbsp;<u>you still currently hold an active annual policy of insurance with Kingsbridge</u>.</div><div style="font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><b>The period your policy is due to be active&nbsp;<i>(DDMMYYYY to DDMMYYYY)</i>.&nbsp;<br></b><br><br><b style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Important information regarding your insurance cover</b><br><br><font face="arial">IR35 Protect operates on a ‘claims made’ basis, so the policy must be active to respond to most claims. However, for&nbsp;</font><a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">sections 10-12</a><font face="arial">&nbsp;on your policy there is a 4-year extended reporting period for you to notify us of a claim for an investigation during the period your policy was active</font><font face="arial">. Any claim in these sections must be notified to insurers within 30 days of an insured event taking place and before any response to HMRC. Your appointed representation will work with you to respond and manage communications with HMRC.</font><br><br><br><b style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Please confirm you still wish to cancel</b><br><br><font face="arial">Whilst you consider whether you would like to proceed with your cancellation,&nbsp;</font><u style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">we have removed your policy from auto-renewal</u><font face="arial">. This means your insurance policy will expire on&nbsp;</font><i style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">(DD MM YY)</i><font face="arial">.</font><br><br><font face="arial">If you are&nbsp;</font><u style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">happy to proceed with your cancellation based on the information above, please confirm by replying to this email within 7 days</u><font face="arial">.</font><br><br><br><font face="arial">Whether you’re currently insured with Kingsbridge or not, our customer service team is always here to help. Please don’t hesitate to reply to this email if you need any further information on any of the above.</font><br><font style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br>Kind regards,<br></font><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br>{!User.FirstName}<br></span><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Customer Service Team<br></span><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br>E:&nbsp;</span><a href="mailto:customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</a><br><span style="font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">T: 01242 808 740</span></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>